I think the only supports that are in need of change are {{champion:37}} {{champion:89}} {{champion:267}}. Nami just feels like a worse {{champion:40}}/{{champion:16}}. Leona, just makes me want to puke. The only champion to date that I can say I've never had fun playing. She, like essentially every champion I've listed needing change is only good if ahead. {{champion:37}} like I've said is only good when ahead. She loses in late game 9 times out of 10.

I agree that supports need more options and itemization. Essentially every game, I go the same build on every support I play, aside from maybe Sona, Annie, or Lux.

{{item:2303}} / {{item:3092}} {{item:2049}}   
 into
{{item:3009}} /{{item:3158}} 
then
{{item:3060}} /{{item:3190}} 
then whatever i feel i need to win the game.

The strong get stronger, and the weak get weaker...until the strong completely die out then the weak come out of hiding as OP as they were always meant to be.

Until that day, sleep with the fishes, my love.{{champion:267}} 

Rip my dead love{{champion:143}}
